{
  "stem": "2966.2",
  "chunk_idx": 8,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.2,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "And they took them-- at that time, we knew already-- they took them to Belzec, where they had crematoriums already built.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, Christian people who were traveling and going, and maybe somebody had a hidden radio.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "You know, news travels a little bit, even though we had-- didn't have too many connections or-- with the Christian people because they were afraid.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And-- and-- but news did travel.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Some people had more connections, and some people and less.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Some people still worked in the oil industry on the oil wells, where-- which was very important for the Germans.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And there they met with their coworkers.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "They still also-- which I didn't mention, you see, that we had to wear-- immediately when the Germans came in, in 1941, we had to wear armband, a white band on the left arm with a Jewish star, in blue.",
      "word_count": 40
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And you were not allowed to go anyplace without it.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "At all times you had to wear it.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "You didn't wear it, if they caught you, you could have been killed immediately, or sent away someplace.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "There was no lighter penalty.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] In August of 1942, I saw happen that my father was supposed to have been working in a store in the middle of the town.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "The store was completely empty and some German was going to open up a store there, whatever it was.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "We had the keys to it.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "My father had the key.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Well, we went there.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And we hid in that store, locked up, so nobody-- nobody knew we were there.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "As matter of fact, one of the aunts was with us, too.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] And we were sitting there in the attic.",
      "word_count": 12
    }
  ],
